4 slice Sourdough Bread
4 ounce Pineapple
1 unit Tomato
¼ ounce Cilantro
1 unit Lime
1 cup Guacamole
1.5 ounce Blue Corn Tortilla Chips
Salt
Pepper

• Wash and dry produce.

• Toast bread. Drain pineapple. Dice tomato into ½-inch pieces. Roughly
chop cilantro. Quarter lime.

• In a small bowl, combine pineapple, tomato, cilantro, and juice from
one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings); season lightly with salt
and pepper.

• Evenly spread guacamole on toasts; season with a pinch of salt and
pepper. Top with pineapple salsa.

• Divide avocado toasts between plates. Gently crush tortilla chips over
tops and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.